{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/anicolson/DeepXi/issues/22","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/anicolson/DeepXi","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/anicolson/DeepXi/issues/22/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/anicolson/DeepXi/issues/22/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/anicolson/DeepXi/issues/22/events","html_url":"https://github.com/anicolson/DeepXi/issues/22","id":577318277,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NzczMTgyNzc=","number":22,"title":"Resolve the distortion caused by integer overflow","user":{"login":"20050710212","id":4574648,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1NzQ2NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4574648?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212","html_url":"https://github.com/20050710212","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2020-03-07T10:59:45Z","updated_at":"2020-03-17T10:28:03Z","closed_at":"2020-03-17T10:28:03Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"When the data in the wav files are very big, closing to -32768 or 32767, the data after speech enhancement is likely tobe overflow, thus resulting distortion. I find two places to correct this issue and I hope it works for you. \r\n\r\n1. **utils.py**,  change 32768.0 to 32767.0, since +32768 becomes -32768. More formally, use 32767.0 for positive number and 32768.0 for negative number.\r\n```\r\ndef save_wav(save_path, f_s, wav):\r\n\tif isinstance(wav[0], np.float32): wav = np.asarray(np.multiply(wav, 32767.0), dtype=np.int16)\r\n\twav_write(save_path, f_s, wav)\r\n```\r\n2.  **infer.py**, add `y = np.clip(y,-1,1)` before writing the file, since wav data can not exceed 1.0.\r\n```\r\nelif args.out_type == 'y':\r\n\ty_MAG = np.multiply(input_feat[0], gain.gfunc(xi_hat, xi_hat+1, gtype=args.gain))\r\n\ty = np.squeeze(sess.run(net.y, feed_dict={net.y_MAG_ph: y_MAG, net.x_PHA_ph: input_feat[2], net.nframes_ph: input_feat[1], net.training_ph: False})) # output of network.\r\n\ty = np.clip(y,-1,1)\r\n\tif np.isnan(y).any(): ValueError('NaN values found in enhanced speech.')\r\n\tif np.isinf(y).any(): ValueError('Inf values found in enhanced speech.')\r\n\tutils.save_wav(args.out_path + '/' + file_name + '.wav', args.f_s, y)\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"20050710212","id":4574648,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1NzQ2NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4574648?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212","html_url":"https://github.com/20050710212","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/20050710212/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url